</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1451636-darkwood"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1257369775i/1451636._UY100_CR27,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1451636-darkwood">Darkwood</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The nice Stetson hat was the most tangible clue and it points away from Farish. While he was crazy and mean enough to do something that senseless it d<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The nice Stetson hat was the most tangible clue and it points away from Farish. While he was crazy and mean enough to do something that senseless it doesn't fit his MO at all. My top suspect is Roy Dial who might wear an expensive Stetson. The sisters' properties would certainly be attractive to him. Robin was their only male heir and might eventually stand in the way of his attaining their properties. The heart shaped candy box that Edie kept the pictures of Robin in smacks of Roy Dial's habit of hovering about a misfortune and bringing little tokens of his sympathy. The only other character in the book who might wear a nice Stetson was J. Rhodes Sumner, but he was introduced late in the book and as we know who killed Cock Robin was revealed in the first stanza.<br />The verse Dial was quoting in Sunday school class was "I am a voice of one crying out in the wilderness: Make straight the way of the Lord". And his point was that you have to have a plan or in his case a scheme. It's in this scene that Dial is described as having a "bulging forehead" which might well require a size 8 black dress hat.<br />Libby found the hat at the foot of her bed and perhaps where Libby kept her cedar chest and where she had indicated to Odean that she would find her share of Libby's estate. It's not much of a stretch to think that Mr. Dial discovered that Robin was the principle heir and decided that it was part of God's plan for him to strangle Robin and hang him in the tree.<br /><a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
